parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear backup camera can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when reversing.
symptoms: The rear backup camera displays a pink or multicolored screen
the camera image is blurry or distorted
the camera fails to display an image
the camera only works intermittently
the camera fails to work after opening and shutting the rear hatch.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unexpected Acceleration and Cruise Control Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unexpected acceleration and cruise control malfunctions can cause loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the cruise control does not work correctly
the vehicle speeds up after taking foot off the accelerator
the vehicle accelerates between foot pedal braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: GPS and Charging Station Navigation Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctioning GPS and charging station navigation can cause inconvenience, delay, and potentially strand drivers, especially those relying on electric vehicles.
symptoms: The GPS system provides incorrect or outdated information
the charging station navigation system is not dynamic
the system displays "out of range" status despite being within range.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A sudden drop in battery percentage can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The battery gauge suddenly drops from a normal level to a low level
often accompanied by a warning light.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Airbag Deployment and Loss of Vehicle Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unexpected deployment of airbags can cause loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The airbags deploy unexpectedly
often accompanied by a loss of steering and braking functionality.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Forward Camera Overheating and Collision Avoidance System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the forward camera and collision avoidance system can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle reports that the forward camera is overheating
rendering the collision avoidance system and ProPilot inoperative.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration while using Adaptive Cruise Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle while using adaptive cruise control can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially in stop-and-go traffic or when following another vehicle closely.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without input from the driver
often when using adaptive cruise control in specific conditions such as light rain or intermittent wiper use
and may require manual braking to avoid a collision.
